AgentClash CLI is the command-line interface for the AgentClash platform.

Manage organizations, workspaces, agent builds, deployments, evaluation runs,
challenge packs, playgrounds, and infrastructure — all from your terminal.

Get started:
  agentclash auth login         Log in to your account
  agentclash workspace use      Set your default workspace
  agentclash run create         Create an evaluation run
  agentclash run events <id>    Stream live run events

Usage:
  agentclash [command]

Available Commands:
  artifact       Upload and download artifacts
  auth           Manage authentication
  build          Manage agent builds
  challenge-pack Manage challenge packs
  compare        Compare runs and evaluate release gates
  completion     Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  config         Manage CLI configuration
  deployment     Manage agent deployments
  eval           Race deployed models on a challenge pack and print a scorecard
  help           Help about any command
  infra          Manage infrastructure resources
  init           Initialize a project with .agentclash.yaml
  link           Link this directory to your AgentClash workspace
  org            Manage organizations
  playground     Manage playgrounds, test cases, and experiments
  replay         View execution replays
  run            Manage evaluation runs
  secret         Manage workspace secrets
  version        Show CLI version information
  workspace      Manage workspaces

Flags:
      --api-url string     API base URL (overrides config)
  -h, --help               help for agentclash
      --json               Output in JSON format
      --no-color           Disable color output
      --non-interactive    Disable interactive prompts (also honored: CI=true, AGENTCLASH_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, --json, no TTY)
  -o, --output string      Output format: table, json, yaml
  -q, --quiet              Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose            Enable debug output on stderr
  -w, --workspace string   Workspace ID (overrides config)
      --yes                Skip confirmation prompts

Use "agentclash [command] --help" for more information about a command.
